<Page
    x:Class="InternetBankCalculator.MainframeModernizationPage"
    xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
    Background="#F5F7FA">

    <ScrollViewer>
        <StackPanel MaxWidth="800"
                    Margin="24"
                    Spacing="32">
            <TextBlock Text="AS/400 (IBM i) in the Cloud &amp; COBOL Modernization"
                       FontSize="28"
                       FontWeight="Bold"
                       Margin="0,0,0,12"/>

            <StackPanel Spacing="12">
                <TextBlock Text="Cloud Providers for AS/400 (IBM i)"
                           FontSize="22"
                           FontWeight="SemiBold"/>
                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                    IBM i (AS/400) workloads can be hosted in the cloud using specialized offerings:
                </TextBlock>
                <StackPanel Spacing="8">
                    <TextBlock Text="• IBM Cloud: IBM Power Systems Virtual Server runs IBM i, AIX, and Linux workloads natively."/>
                    <TextBlock Text="• Microsoft Azure: Skytap on Azure allows running IBM i, AIX, and Power workloads in Azure with minimal changes."/>
                    <TextBlock Text="• Google Cloud: Skytap (via partner) can also host IBM i workloads, but is less common than Azure or IBM Cloud."/>
                </StackPanel>
            </StackPanel>

            <StackPanel Spacing="12">
                <TextBlock Text="Modernizing COBOL/AS400 Systems"
                           FontSize="22"
                           FontWeight="SemiBold"/>
                <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                    There are several strategies to modernize COBOL and AS/400 workloads:
                </TextBlock>
                <StackPanel Spacing="8">
                    <TextBlock Text="• Rehosting: Move existing workloads to cloud VMs or managed Power Systems (IBM Cloud, Azure Skytap) without code changes."/>
                    <TextBlock Text="• Refactoring: Use automated tools to convert COBOL to modern languages (Java, C#). Vendors: Micro Focus, Astadia, Heirloom Computing."/>
                    <TextBlock Text="• API Enablement: Expose mainframe business logic as REST APIs using IBM z/OS Connect or third-party API gateways."/>
                    <TextBlock Text="• Rewrite: Manually rewrite business logic in a modern language/framework (Java, .NET), often using microservices."/>
                    <TextBlock Text="• Hybrid: Gradually decompose the monolith, keeping core logic on IBM i while building new features in the cloud."/>
                </StackPanel>
            </StackPanel>

            <StackPanel Spacing="12">
                <TextBlock Text="References &amp; Tools"
                           FontSize="18"
                           FontWeight="SemiBold"/>
                <StackPanel Spacing="4">
                    <HyperlinkButton Content="IBM Power Systems Virtual Server"
                                     NavigateUri="https://www.ibm.com/cloud/power-virtual-server"
                                     FontSize="16"
                                     Foreground="#0078D7"
                                     ToolTipService.ToolTip="Open IBM Power Systems Virtual Server"/>
                    <HyperlinkButton Content="Skytap on Azure"
                                     NavigateUri="https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/products/skytap/"
                                     FontSize="16"
                                     Foreground="#0078D7"
                                     ToolTipService.ToolTip="Open Skytap on Azure"/>
                    <HyperlinkButton Content="Micro Focus COBOL Modernization"
                                     NavigateUri="https://www.microfocus.com/en-us/solutions/modernization"
                                     FontSize="16"
                                     Foreground="#0078D7"
                                     ToolTipService.ToolTip="Open Micro Focus COBOL Modernization"/>
                    <HyperlinkButton Content="Heirloom Computing"
                                     NavigateUri="https://www.heirloomcomputing.com/"
                                     FontSize="16"
                                     Foreground="#0078D7"
                                     ToolTipService.ToolTip="Open Heirloom Computing"/>
                    <HyperlinkButton Content="Astadia Mainframe Migration"
                                     NavigateUri="https://astadia.com/"
                                     FontSize="16"
                                     Foreground="#0078D7"
                                     ToolTipService.ToolTip="Open Astadia Mainframe Migration"/>
                </StackPanel>
            </StackPanel>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
